alwaysApply: true
---

This folder is an app in a monorepo. All packages inside the monorepo use NPM workspaces.
Use `pnpm` instead of `npm`, because PNPM works better with monorepo workspaces.

Path to this app is `./apps/data`. Path from this app to the monorepo root is `../../`.

This app uses NextJS version. It focuses on managing user accounts, visualizes and manages database tables and content. It manages all data for all apps, not only related to user accounts but also logs, orders, trades, and other stuff.

This app is a central hub of common reusable functionality imported by all other apps in the monorepo. Files in this project are imported by other apps. So, treat this app as a common utility library. Do not import files using project-relative shortcuts like `@/components/Button` but instead use always use relative paths like `../../../components/Button`.

- ./apps/data/sql - implementation and itegration of the database - most tables use Prisma DB - connect to PRISMA_DATABASE_URL via ./apps/data/lib/prisma.ts and ./apps/data/prisma/schema.prisma

- ./apps/data/sql/fractal - uses Neon DB - connects to NEON_DATABASE_URL via ./apps/data/lib/neon.ts
